data.text:
opopanax

Opopanax, also known as sweet myrrh, is a type of resin that comes from a variety of different plants, particularly plants in the genera Commiphora and Busera. This resin has a sweet, balsamic fragrance and is often used in perfumery and aromatherapy. Additionally, it has been traditionally used in herbal medicine for its supposed anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties.
